description: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the FTSE Custom Emerging Ultra Dividend Revenue Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as ADRs and GDRs that represent securities in the underlying index. The underlying index includes a subset of constituent securities of the FTSE Emerging Index, an index designed to represent the performance of securities of the most liquid large- and mid-capitalization companies in emerging market countries. The fund is non-diversified.
name: Invesco Emerging Markets Ultra Dividend Revenue ETF
